==English==

=== Etymology ===
From {{etymon|la|ululare|ululāre}} "to howl", of imitative origin.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈjuːljuleɪt/ or /ˈʊljəleɪt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-ululate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|ululat|ing}}

# to [[howl]] loudly or prolongedly in [[lamentation]] or [[joy]]

====Synonyms====
*(''to howl''): [[bay]], [[howl]], [[wail]]

